## Compatibility Testing

### 1. Device Compatibility
- Test on various Android versions
- Verify on different screen sizes
- Check tablet compatibility
- Test on low-end devices

### 2. Play Store Requirements
- Target API level compliance
- Privacy policy
- Content rating
- App permissions justification

## Common Issues and Solutions

### 1. Device Incompatibility
- Make hardware features optional
- Support all screen sizes
- Include all necessary ABIs
- Test with Play Console device catalog

### 2. Release Rejection
- Review content policies
- Check metadata requirements
- Verify privacy compliance
- Address permission issues

### 3. Rating Issues
- Proper content rating
- Age-appropriate content
- Clear feature descriptions

## Best Practices

### 1. Version Management
- Consistent version numbering
- Clear changelog format
- Beta testing strategy

### 2. Store Presence
- Regular updates
- Respond to reviews
- Monitor analytics
- Track user feedback

### 3. Release Strategy
- Staged rollouts
- A/B testing
- Beta program management
- Update frequency

## Testing Tracks

### 1. Internal Testing
- Limited to specific users
- Quick iteration
- Immediate updates

### 2. Closed Testing
- Selected test group
- Focused feedback
- Pre-release validation

### 3. Open Testing
- Public beta testing
- Wider feedback range
- Final pre-release stage

## Documentation

### 1. Version History
- Keep detailed changelogs
- Document API changes
- Track compatibility updates

### 2. Known Issues
- Document workarounds
- Track bug reports
- Plan future fixes
